No shelter. Only my shaking arms and silent prayers. We have lost everything. Our home is gone. Our lives destroyed. I search every day for anything anything to ease his pain, but there is nothing. Now, I am watching my baby fade before my eyes. And I can do nothing. Please… if you are reading this… I am begging you from the deepest place of a mother’s agony: help us. Even the smallest kindness could be the difference between life and death. One meal. One bottle of medicine. One heartbeat more. Please don’t turn away. Please don’t let my child die without being seen. Let your mercy reach us. Let him live to see another day
